# CHANGELOGS

## 1.0.2
- Update environment variable formatting: refine warning message for missing keys
- Add expected values for tests

## 1.0.1 (May 8, 2025)
- Enhance git ignore status check: handle command not found and specific exit codes
- Add GitHub release badge to README files

## 1.0.0 (May 8, 2025)
- Update build configuration: enhance versioning and remove redundant variables
- Fix archive format configuration to use 'zip' for all platforms
- Update GoReleaser action to version 6 in workflow configuration
- Fix build configuration: reorder OS and architecture settings in .goreleaser.yaml
- Enhance build process by adding environment variables for build time and commit hash
- Update Go application versioning to reflect these changes
- Refactor: Remove redundant comments and improve code clarity across multiple files
- Refactor: Enhance color formatting utilities and add comprehensive tests
- Implement structural updates and optimizations across multiple modules
- Refactor logging calls to use formatted strings for message formatting

> **BREAKING CHANGE**: Default input file name changed from `env` to `.env`

## 2024.03.15 (March 15, 2024)
- Fix CRLF issue

## 2024.03.13 (March 13, 2024)
- Fix environment variable specification to use ExportName
- Update .gitignore
- Change .cache.env permissions to 644 and make it automatically added to .gitignore

## 2023.12.06 (December 6, 2023)
- Change binary name for consistency
- Add Homebrew release support
- Update Go version to 1.20 for GitHub Actions compatibility
- Remove toolchain specification
- Add GoReleaser workflow and settings

## Initial Development (November - December 2023)
- Fix plain text formatting and remove newlines from Google Cloud secrets
